meanings.definition: アルベルト・シュヴァイツァー (人名: 1875-1965, ドイツの神学者、医師、音楽家、哲学者、ノーベル平和賞受賞者)
meanings.english_definition: Albert Schweitzer (1875–1965), a German theologian, physician, musician, philosopher, and Nobel Peace Prize laureate.
examples: Albert Schweitzer was a renowned humanitarian.

etymology.value: The surname is of German origin.
